<title>ZAMBIA: ZCCM miners reject wage offer, talks go on.</title>
<headline>ZCCM miners reject wage offer, talks go on.</headline>
<dateline>LUSAKA 1997-07-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Mineworkers Union of Zambia said on Tuesday it had rejected a wage offer by Zambia Consolidated Copper Mines, but would continue negotiations.</p>
<p>&quot;Management made us an offer for salary increases, but we rejected it,&quot; a senior official of the 42,000-member union told Reuters.</p>
<p>&quot;The wage negotiations will continue until we reach a compromise,&quot; the official said.</p>
<p>He declined to say what increase the government had proposed.</p>
<p>Miners threatened to strike last month over low wages after the cash-strapped ZCCM, in the process of privatising its assets, said it would not give salary increases this year.</p>
<p>Management responded by calling for wage talks on Tuesday.</p>
